Intraspecific variation is limited in the material (
Fig. 6B–E
), but the cardinal conch parameters show some ontogenetic changes in the growth interval between 20 and 
85 mm
conch diameter: (1) the ww/ dm ratio increases slowly from an average of 0.38 to 0.42 (
Fig. 6B
), (2) the uw/dm ratio decreases from nearly 0.50 to 0.38 (
Fig. 6C
), (3) the ww/wh ratio decreases from 1.20 to 1.00 (
Fig. 6D
) and (4) the whorl expansion rate shows a more prominent increase from 2.20 to 2.80 (
Fig. 6E
).

Variation in the ornament is also limited. The change from the third to the fourth ornament stage, for instance, takes place between 37 and 
42 mm
conch diameter in specimens MB.C.30379.4 (
Fig. 5B
), MB.C.30379.2 (
Fig. 4B
) and MB.C.30379.3 (
Fig. 5A
).
